## 📋 Recipe 1: SaaS App
**Stack**: Next.js + TypeScript → Supabase → Stripe → Resend → Netlify
**Time**: 30–45 minutes

### Phase 1 — Foundation
```
Build a SaaS called "[Name]" using Next.js and TypeScript.
Pages: landing page with hero and feature sections, pricing page with Free
and Pro tiers, /login, /signup, /dashboard with sidebar, /settings.
Clean modern design with [color] primary. Responsive navbar with logo,
nav links, and login/signup buttons.
```

### Phase 2 — Database
```
Connect Supabase. Create these tables:
1. profiles — id (uuid, references auth.users), display_name (text),
   avatar_url (text), created_at (timestamp)
2. [your main data table] — id, user_id (references profiles),
   [fields], created_at, updated_at
Add RLS: users can only access their own rows where user_id = auth.uid().
Create a trigger that auto-inserts a profiles row when a new user signs up.
```

### Phase 3 — Auth
```
Implement Supabase Auth:
- email/password signup + login
- forgot password flow
- protect /dashboard and /settings — redirect unauthenticated to /login
- user menu in top-right with avatar, name, and sign-out
```

### Phase 4 — Stripe
```
Connect Stripe test keys. Create a $[price]/month "[Plan Name]" subscription.
Webhook handler at /api/webhooks/stripe for:
checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.updated,
customer.subscription.deleted.
On checkout complete → update user plan in Supabase 'subscriptions' table.
Store Stripe customer ID and subscription ID.
Add a billing page in settings showing current plan and "Manage Subscription"
button linking to Stripe Customer Portal.
```

### Phase 5 — Email
```
Connect Resend. Send:
- Welcome email on signup: greeting with user name + dashboard link
- Receipt email after Stripe checkout: plan name, amount, billing date
```

### Phase 6 — Deploy
```
Deploy to Netlify. After deploying, add these redirect URLs to
Supabase Auth → URL Configuration:
https://[your-app].netlify.app
https://[your-custom-domain.com]
```

### ⚠️ Go-Live Checklist
- [ ] Recreate Stripe products/prices in LIVE mode (test mode items don't transfer)
- [ ] Switch from Stripe test keys to live keys in env vars
- [ ] Update Stripe webhook endpoint URL to production URL
- [ ] Update Stripe webhook secret in Netlify env vars (live secret differs from test)
- [ ] Add production URL to Supabase redirect URLs
- [ ] Enable Supabase email confirmations to prevent spam signups

