## 📋 Recipe 2: E-Commerce Store
**Stack**: Next.js + TypeScript → Supabase → Stripe → SendGrid → Google Analytics → Netlify

### Build Sequence
```
Phase 1:
Create an online store with Next.js. Pages: /products (grid),
/products/[slug] (detail), /cart, /checkout, /order-confirmation.
Responsive design with a clean, minimal aesthetic.

Phase 2:
Connect Supabase. Create tables:
- products: id, name (text), description (text), price (decimal),
  image_url (text), inventory (integer), category (text), slug (text unique)
- orders: id, user_id, status (text), total (decimal), created_at
- order_items: id, order_id, product_id, quantity, price_at_purchase
Add RLS: users can read all products, read/create only their own orders.

Phase 3:
Connect Stripe. Add checkout with:
- line items from the cart
- success_url: /order-confirmation?session_id={CHECKOUT_SESSION_ID}
- cancel_url: /cart
Webhook: on checkout.session.completed → create order + order_items in Supabase,
update inventory.

Phase 4:
Connect SendGrid. Send order confirmation email on checkout.session.completed.
Include: order ID, list of items, total, estimated delivery.
```

